The returned array `arr` is not null.
The length of the returned array `arr` is the same as the input array `nums`.
The returned array `arr` contains all the integers from the input array `nums`.
The returned array `arr` contains exactly half of the integers from the input array `nums` that are present in `lower`.
The returned array `arr` contains the remaining half of the integers from the input array `nums` that are present in `higher`.
The returned array `arr` is a valid original array that satisfies the given requirements.
If there are multiple valid original arrays, the method can return any of them.
